New Records: De’Aaron Fox’s 109 points are the most over a two-game span in franchise history, passing DeMarcus Cousins.
Key Match Events: De’Aaron Fox scored 49 points to lead the Sacramento Kings to a 121-117 victory over the Utah Jazz.
Fox went 16 of 30 from the field and made 14 of 19 from the free-throw line, and he added nine assists and two steals.
The Kings trailed 89-78 in the third quarter but took a 118-116 lead on a Jordan McLaughlin 3-pointer with 1:04 remaining.
Miscellaneous Highlights: Both teams shot basically the same percentage from 3-point range. The Kings made 19 of 41 shots, or 46.3%, from beyond the arc. The Jazz shot 12 for 26, or 46.2%.
